title: Spitfire - Frontline Fighter
description:
This unique title collects together four previously unreleased wartime films featuring the Supermarine Spitfire. Together, they offer a detailed, close up look at the aircraft as operated by the RAF throughout the war years. 

&#039;The Daily Inspection Of A Spitfire&#039; provides a technical walkround of the Spitfire MK I, while &#039;1940&#039;s Re-Arming&#039; shows the rapid re-fuelling and re-arming of a flight of Spitfires. 

&#039;Spitfire&#039; is a 1944 aircraft recognition film packed with great footage of the Mark I, V, XIV and XXI and Seafire. 

Finally, written by Air Marshal Sir Phillip Joubert in 1940, &#039;Fighter Pilot&#039; is a short film celebrating the Spitfire at the height of the Battle of Britain.
